nload PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5829121\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5829121\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jyy1705583151243.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jyy1705583151243.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jyy1705583151243.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ivr1665702687878\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Working with Panels \n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Panels are global objects that are used to define toolbars or floating palettes in desktop applications. They can be associated with a form component or an application shell.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__context_w4037ab1b5b1_w4038ab1b5_w4039ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__topic_d26852e1_d26853e1_d26854e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__p_d26855e1_d26856e1_d26857e1\">Each button in a panel can activate an operation or structure editor function. Operation buttons can only be used in form panels. Panels can also contain separators and multiple lines.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13562e1_d13563e1_d13564e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Editors</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Panels</span></span>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__p_d26858e1_d26859e1_d26860e1\">In the Open Panel dialog, select the library to\n               hold the panel, and select an existing panel to edit or enter a new name to create a\n               new panel. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">This opens the panel in the panel editor (Define Panel).</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__fig_d26861e1_d26862e1_d26863e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__fig_w4043ab1b5b3b3b3b1b1b1_w4044ab1b5b3b3b3b1b1_w4045ab1b5b3b3b3b1_w4046ab1b5b3b3b3_w4047ab1b5b3b3_w4048ab1b5b3_w4049ab1b5_w4050ab1\">\n<img alt=\"Panel editor\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/paneleditor.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13568e1_d13569e1_d13570e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To create a new panel or open another panel for editing, choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">New</span> or <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Open</span> in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File</span> menu.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13571e1_d13572e1_d13573e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__p_d26864e1_d26865e1_d26866e1\">To add a button that invokes a structure editor\n               functions, select it in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Function</span> list and click\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Add</span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">This automatically sets the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Glyph &amp; Message Text</span>\n                  property, which provides the icon and tooltip.</p>\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__note_w4051ab1b5b3b7b3b1_w4052ab1b5b3b7b3_w4053ab1b5b3b7_w4054ab1b5b3_w4055ab1b5_w4056ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> It is recommended that you define fewer than ten functions in a\n                  panel.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13574e1_d13575e1_d13576e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To add an operation button to a form panel:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13577e1_d13578e1_d13579e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Select <code class=\"ph codeph\">Activate Operation</code> from the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Function</span> list.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13580e1_d13581e1_d13582e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__p_d26867e1_d26868e1_d26869e1\">In the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Operation</span>\n                     property, specify the name of an operation defined in the component's\n                     Operations container.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\"> If an operation button refers to an operation that does not exist in its\n                        current context, the button is disabled.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__note_w4057ab1b5b3b9b3b3b3b1_w4058ab1b5b3b9b3b3b3_w4059ab1b5b3b9b3b3_w4060ab1b5b3b9b3_w4061ab1b5b3b9_w4062ab1b5b3_w4063ab1b5_w4064ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Operation buttons are not displayed\n      if the panel is used as a pop-up panel.</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13583e1_d13584e1_d13585e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__p_d26870e1_d26871e1_d26872e1\">In the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Glyph &amp; Message\n                        Text</span> property, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">&gt;&gt;</span> and select\n                     the glyph you want to use for the operation button. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">If a message of the same name exists, it is automatically associated with\n                        the glyph.</p>\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__note_w4065ab1b5b3b9b3b5b3b1_w4066ab1b5b3b9b3b5b3_w4067ab1b5b3b9b3b5_w4068ab1b5b3b9b3_w4069ab1b5b3b9_w4070ab1b5b3_w4071ab1b5_w4072ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> If you have not yet defined a glyph and tooltip message for the\n                        button, you can open the Glyph and Message editors from the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Go\n                           To</span> menu.</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13586e1_d13587e1_d13588e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If the panel is to be used as a session panel, set the following properties:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13589e1_d13590e1_d13591e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vkx1665702687952.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vkx1665702687952.html\" title=\"This property determines whether buttons for character attributes (bold, italics, and underline) are displayed when the panel is used as a session panel. Valid values are True or False.\">Character Attributes</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13592e1_d13593e1_d13594e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xmm1665702688023.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xmm1665702688023.html\" title=\"Determines whether buttons for View, Overstrike, and Previous mode should appear in the panel when it is used as a session panel.\">View</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13595e1_d13596e1_d13597e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zga1665702688096.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zga1665702688096.html\" title=\"Number of available Uniface character sets (Font 0 through Font 7) for which a button is displayed when this panel is used as a session panel. Valid values are 0 through 7.\">Font Range</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13598e1_d13599e1_d13600e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__p_d26873e1_d26874e1_d26875e1\">To save (and compile) the panel, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Save</span></span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Alternatively, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span> to save the panel and close the\n                  editor.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13601e1_d13602e1_d13603e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To delete the panel, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Delete</span></span>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13604e1_d13605e1_d13606e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To use a panel in a form or application shell:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13607e1_d13608e1_d13609e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In a Form component, specify the panel in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Panel</span> property.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13610e1_d13611e1_d13612e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__p_d26876e1_d26877e1_d26878e1\">In a Windows or character-based application\n                     shell, specify a pop-up panel in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Panel</span> property and\n                     a session panel in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Session Panel</span> property. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Only a Windows application shell can have more than one panel assigned.</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13613e1_d13614e1_d13615e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Panel Position</span> to determine where the form or session panel is displayed.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13616e1_d13617e1_d13618e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__p_d26879e1_d26880e1_d26881e1\">To control the appearance of the panels in\n               Windows applications, edit the following settings in the application initialization\n               file (<span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span>). </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13619e1_d13620e1_d13621e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"avj1665702614940.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/avj1665702614940.html\" title=\"Specifies a style for the appearance of buttons and borders in the Uniface toolbar and panels.\">ButtonStyle</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13622e1_d13623e1_d13624e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vpp1665702671467.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vpp1665702671467.html\" title=\"Set the color and border properties for all panels and toolbars in the application.\">Panel</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13625e1_d13626e1_d13627e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fbn1665702616587.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fbn1665702616587.html\" title=\"Determines the background color of panels.\">PanelColor</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">For example, to define your own color scheme:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13628e1_d13629e1_d13630e1\">Set <code class=\"ph codeph\">ButtonStyle=9</code>\n                     (User-defined) </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__li_d13631e1_d13632e1_d13633e1\">Set the color properties using the\n                        <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Panel</span> setting in the [application] section. </li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__p_d26882e1_d26883e1_d26884e1\">(For readability, this example is formatted over\n                  several lines)</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;usys.ini\n[application]\nPanel = upanel(backcolor=#fdfdfd;forecolor=black;forecolorselect=green;\n backcolorselect=#c0ddfc;bordercolorselect=#3399ff;\n backcolorfill=gradient)\n[upi]\nButtonStyle=9</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__result_w4040ab1b5b5_w4041ab1b5_w4042ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv postreq\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__topic_d26885e1_d26886e1_d26887e1\">\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"ivr1665702687878__note_w4073ab1b5b5b1b1_w4074ab1b5b5b1_w4075ab1b5b5_w4076ab1b5_w4077ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> If the panel is not displayed during testing or deployment, ensure that\n               the assignment file contains a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$VARIATION</span> setting that specifies\n               the library that contains the panel.</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cpe1705582470714.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Create and Maintain Glyphs</a><p>Glyphs are maintained and deployed in a runtime library.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eiq1705568671736.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Working with Messages</a><p>Create messages to define named text blocks that can be used in labels and messages.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fcq1665703251101.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$VARIATION</a><p>Specify the library name for global objects needed by the application when the application starts. Libraries are typed, so each global object library can have the same name which functions as a shared namespace which can be specified by this setting.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5829121\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5829121\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Working with Panels Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Working with Panels Panels are global objects that are used to define toolbars or floating palettes in desktop applications. They can be associated with a form component or an application shell. Each button in a panel can activate an operation or structure editor function. Operation buttons can only be used in form panels. Panels can also contain separators and multiple lines. Choose More Editors > Panels . In the Open Panel dialog, select the library to hold the panel, and select an existing panel to edit or enter a new name to create a new panel. This opens the panel in the panel editor (Define Panel). To create a new panel or open another panel for editing, choose New or Open in the File menu. To add a button that invokes a structure editor functions, select it in the Function list and click Add . This automatically sets the Glyph & Message Text property, which provides the icon and tooltip. Tip: It is recommended that you define fewer than ten functions in a panel. To add an operation button to a form panel: Select Activate Operation from the Function list. In the Operation property, specify the name of an operation defined in the component's Operations container. If an operation button refers to an operation that does not exist in its current context, the button is disabled. Note: Operation buttons are not displayed if the panel is used as a pop-up panel. In the Glyph & Message Text property, click >> and select the glyph you want to use for the operation button. If a message of the same name exists, it is automatically associated with the glyph. Tip: If you have not yet defined a glyph and tooltip message for the button, you can open the Glyph and Message editors from the Go To menu. If the panel is to be used as a session panel, set the following properties: Character Attributes View Font Range To save (and compile) the panel, choose File > Save . Alternatively, click OK to save the panel and close the editor. To delete the panel, choose File > Delete . To use a panel in a form or application shell: In a Form component, specify the panel in the Panel property. In a Windows or character-based application shell, specify a pop-up panel in the Panel property and a session panel in the Session Panel property. Only a Windows application shell can have more than one panel assigned. Set the Panel Position to determine where the form or session panel is displayed. To control the appearance of the panels in Windows applications, edit the following settings in the application initialization file ( usys.ini ). ButtonStyle Panel PanelColor For example, to define your own color scheme: Set ButtonStyle=9 (User-defined) Set the color properties using the Panel setting in the [application] section. (For readability, this example is formatted over several lines) ;usys.ini [application] Panel = upanel(backcolor=#fdfdfd;forecolor=black;forecolorselect=green; backcolorselect=#c0ddfc;bordercolorselect=#3399ff; backcolorfill=gradient) [upi] ButtonStyle=9 Copy Tip: If the panel is not displayed during testing or deployment, ensure that the assignment file contains a $VARIATION setting that specifies the library that contains the panel. Related Links Create and Maintain Glyphs Glyphs are maintained and deployed in a runtime library. Working with Messages Create messages to define named text blocks that can be used in labels and messages. $VARIATION Specify the library name for global objects needed by the application when the application starts. Libraries are typed, so each global object library can have the same name which functions as a shared namespace which can be specified by this setting. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}